title: Pretty good
comment: I am a podcast addict so this means I can listen to even more. It works well with podkicker pro. It does drain the battery though.

title: Battery killer!
comment: Works great with AntennaPod but I noticed my battery draining a lot. I went into battery settings and Prestissimo used 21% but AntennaPod only used 12%. Love the faster playback but not enough for that.

title: Speeds up but not down?
comment: Thanks for a free upgrade to my podcast player.  But why can I only speed out playback incrementally, and not step down, too?  Otherwise OK.

title: Depletes the battery

title: Less lag than sonic library
comment: This seems to have less lag than what BeyondPod uses natively.  For those whining about the $4 that aocate was charging for presto, think about this. He put forth a lot of work and released something that was pretty rare. You should be grateful for this package.  I have spent about $20 on Pod catchers and speed tools.  Don't spit on a developer for tying to make a living.

title: Works great with DoggCatcher!
comment: Works wonderfully with DoggCatcher for speedy playback.  Much better value than Presto plugin and its ridiculous price.  Thanks!!

title: Works!
comment: Tried the paid P***** app, which didn't work. Got a refund and tried this instead. Worked first time - brilliant!

title: Excellent free option

title: Perfect!
comment: Does exactly what I was looking for. No bells and whistles, as I didn't need any.

title: Great free alternative.
comment: I can't thank you enough. I was holding off on buying Presto because of the price. Just installed this and it's working great. Playing at 2x speed on BeyondPod and breezing through podcasts I have been falling behind on. Great work and I hope DoggCatcher and BeyondPod are watching so they can give their customers an option to paying almost as much or more for Presto than they did for their app.

title: Responsive Dev
comment: I was having trouble on Dogcatcher where it would stall when changing audio files.  So I submitted an issue on the developers website, and he had a fix released within 24 hours.  Very fast work, I guess that is why he is called TheRealFalcon :)

title: Didn't work
comment: Samsung Galaxy Stellar SCH-I200 with Jellybean  4.1.2and  BeyondPod installed.  BeyondPod recognised the plug-in was there but would not play with it installed. As soon as I removed Prestissmo  BeyondPod began working again.

title: As advertised
